    <h1>From The Coro&#xAD;man&#xAD;del Coast To The Straits &#x2013; Re&#xAD;vis&#xAD;it&#xAD;ing Our Tamil Her&#xAD;itage</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200828/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-28"><time>2020-08-28</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline">WHERE:&#xD;&#xA;MRT: AD&#xAD;MIS&#xAD;SION:&#xD;&#xA;INFO: WHERE: MRT: INFO: WHERE: MRT: INFO: WHEN: WHEN: AD&#xAD;MIS&#xAD;SION: WHEN: AD&#xAD;MIS&#xAD;SION: Arts Cor&#xAD;re&#xAD;spon&#xAD;dent WHERE:&#xD;&#xA;WHEN: AD&#xAD;MIS&#xAD;SION:</span>
    </section>

    <p>This ex­hi­bi­tion by the In­dian Her­itage Cen­tre ex­plores an­cient trade as well as re­li­gious, po­lit­i­cal and cul­tural con­tact be­tween the Tamils of the Coro­man­del Coast in the In­dian sub­con­ti­nent and South-east Asia. It also high­lights the history, cul­ture and con­tri­bu­tions of 19th-cen­tury Tamils in Sin­ga­pore.</p>
    <p>In­dian Her­itage Cen­tre, Spe­cial Ex­hi­bi­tion Gallery, Level 2 Lit­tle In­dia Till Sept 30</p>
    <p>Free for Sin­ga­pore­ans and per­ma­nent res­i­dents</p>
    <p>www.in­di­an­her­itage.org.sg</p>
    <p>A Look Into The Hu­man Psy­che</p>
    <p>Lo­cal multi-me­dia artist duo Par­adise Now, made up of Bryan Tan and Jay Ho, present an ex­hi­bi­tion that ex­plores how one’s per­son­al­ity or self is formed.</p>
    <p>SPRMRKT at Dempsey Hill, 01-15 Block 8 Dempsey Hill</p>
    <p>Botanic Gar­dens Till</p>
    <p>Nov 1, 9am to 10pm daily (open on pub­lic hol­i­days) Free</p>
    <p>sprmrkt.com.sg/pro­gramme/ ex­hi­bi­tions-events</p>
    <p>Thai graf­fiti artist Alex Face shares his po­etic take on the cur­rent state of the world in this ex­hi­bi­tion. The artist cre­ates thought-pro­vok­ing, site-based works in pub­lic spa­ces.</p>
    <p>Art Porters Gallery, 64 Spot­tis­woode Park Road</p>
    <p>Tan­jong Pa­gar Till Sept 6, 10.30am to 7pm daily, Mon­days by ap­point­ment Free</p>
    <p>bit.ly/3jei­idW</p>
    <p>THE COM­PLETE BEETHOVEN VI­O­LIN SONATAS</p>
    <p>Six ac­claimed Sin­ga­porean clas­si­cal mu­si­cians present Beethoven’s Vi­o­lin Sonatas as a com­plete cy­cle in this Face­book con­cert se­ries by More Than Mu­sic.</p>
    <p>Pian­ists Abi­gail Sin (above, left), Al­bert Tiu and Lim Yan and vi­o­lin­ists Loh Jun Hong (above, right), Yang Shux­i­ang and Chan Yoong Han will be paired in dif­fer­ent com­bi­na­tions for each of the 10 sonatas.</p>
    <p>A new sonata will pre­miere every Satur­day and Sun­day on Face­book, with the mu­si­cians avail­able to in­ter­act af­ter­wards with the au­di­ence via live chat.</p>
    <p>More Than Mu­sic co-founder Sin, 28, says: “Pre­sent­ing the com­plete cy­cle of Beethoven Vi­o­lin Sonatas is an am­bi­tious artis­tic undertakin­g and, to our knowl­edge, it hasn’t been done in Sin­ga­pore be­fore.”</p>
    <p>She adds: “The fact that it’s Beethoven’s 250th an­niver­sary this year was the ic­ing on the cake.</p>
    <p>“The Sonatas are a stun­ning ex­plo­ration of the hu­man spirit, tak­ing us on a jour­ney through a huge range of emo­tional states, from high-oc­tane drama to tran­scen­dent lyri­cism.”</p>
    <p>www.face­book.com/</p>
    <p>MoreThanMu­sicCon­certs</p>
    <p>Till Sept 20, every Satur­day and Sun­day, 5pm</p>
    <p>Free</p>

